1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,039
There is a fountain filled with blood, praise God for that.

2
00:00:04,039 --> 00:00:06,099
I've been blessed by the music this morning.

3
00:00:06,099 --> 00:00:08,100
I trust that you have as well.

4
00:00:08,100 --> 00:00:12,819
And I'll say this, you know this, I don't pick the songs.

5
00:00:12,819 --> 00:00:14,720
Brother Dean leads the songs.

6
00:00:14,720 --> 00:00:17,059
I've given him the liberty to be able to pick the songs

7
00:00:17,059 --> 00:00:18,579
throughout these years.

8
00:00:18,579 --> 00:00:21,500
Every once in a while, when it comes to special services

9
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:23,440
and revival meetings and missions conferences,

10
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:27,360
we work together, but regularly he picks the songs.

11
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:29,739
And Dean, there's not a better song

12
00:00:29,739 --> 00:00:31,500
that God could allege you to this morning

13
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:35,060
for our text of scripture than it is well with my soul.

14
00:00:35,060 --> 00:00:37,740
And you think about the difficulties,

15
00:00:37,740 --> 00:00:40,419
if you're familiar with that hymn and Horatio Spafford

16
00:00:40,419 --> 00:00:43,659
and the lost tragic Chicago fire,

17
00:00:43,659 --> 00:00:47,819
and then sending his family and the disaster at sea

18
00:00:47,819 --> 00:00:49,340
and all that took place,

19
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:53,299
but he was able to have God's grace is sufficient.

20
00:00:53,299 --> 00:00:54,979
We've been dealing with it all year.

21
00:00:54,979 --> 00:00:58,939
It's our theme for 2025, God's grace is sufficient.

22
00:00:58,979 --> 00:01:02,459
He's able to pen those words that is well with my soul.

23
00:01:02,459 --> 00:01:06,139
And that song has ministered to countless,

24
00:01:06,139 --> 00:01:09,699
countless, probably millions of Christians

25
00:01:09,699 --> 00:01:13,680
that that song has ministered to since it's writing.

26
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:16,099
And I'm so thankful this morning and it goes so well.

27
00:01:16,099 --> 00:01:19,779
Second Corinthians chapter 12, this morning,

28
00:01:19,779 --> 00:01:21,180
we'll look at verses nine and 10.

29
00:01:21,180 --> 00:01:23,940
Last week, we looked at this text of scripture

30
00:01:23,940 --> 00:01:28,940
and we dealt with as we're studying through this book,

31
00:01:29,059 --> 00:01:31,660
Second Corinthians, our priority on humility

32
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:35,080
and how it was a blessing that the apostle Paul

33
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:37,059
is able to speak to the church in Corinth

34
00:01:37,059 --> 00:01:40,940
and he's able to talk to them about visions and revelations.

35
00:01:40,940 --> 00:01:42,739
But then he talks to him about a thorn

36
00:01:42,739 --> 00:01:44,800
and he talks to him about an answer.

37
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:47,260
And we looked at those three things last week

38
00:01:47,260 --> 00:01:51,059
and specifically I spent some time dealing with a thorn

39
00:01:51,059 --> 00:01:53,779
because the reality is as much as the visions

40
00:01:54,620 --> 00:01:56,980
and revelations were a blessing from God,

41
00:01:56,980 --> 00:02:00,580
the reality is that the thorn too was a gift from God.

42
00:02:00,580 --> 00:02:02,540
It was a blessing from God

43
00:02:02,540 --> 00:02:04,580
because that thorn was given to him.

44
00:02:04,580 --> 00:02:06,379
The Bible tells us he says it twice,

45
00:02:06,379 --> 00:02:09,660
lest I should be exalted above measure.

46
00:02:09,660 --> 00:02:12,779
And there's a priority that God places on humility.

47
00:02:12,779 --> 00:02:16,100
The Bible tells us that God resisteth the proud,

48
00:02:16,100 --> 00:02:18,500
but giveth grace to the humble.

49
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,880
And had those revelations and visions

50
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:23,500
caused the apostle Paul to be prideful,

51
00:02:24,220 --> 00:02:26,740
it would have resulted in God resisting him.

52
00:02:26,740 --> 00:02:30,419
But God gave him as a gift this thorn

53
00:02:30,419 --> 00:02:32,059
that would keep him humble,

54
00:02:32,059 --> 00:02:34,179
that would keep him in a place

55
00:02:34,179 --> 00:02:36,940
lest he be exalted above measure.

56
00:02:36,940 --> 00:02:39,940
And I believe this morning just as I preached last week

57
00:02:39,940 --> 00:02:42,940
that we ought to thank God for the thorn.

58
00:02:42,940 --> 00:02:45,699
He's informed the church not only of the visions,

59
00:02:45,699 --> 00:02:47,779
the revelations, the thorn,

60
00:02:47,779 --> 00:02:49,979
but he informed them of the answer

61
00:02:49,979 --> 00:02:52,919
that God gave to his request for deliverance.

62
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:56,039
In fact, he besought the Lord thrice, the Bible tells us,

63
00:02:56,039 --> 00:02:59,880
and he was desiring the prayer request is simple.

64
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:00,820
It's straightforward.

65
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:02,500
There's nothing complicated

66
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:05,919
that it, the thorn, might depart from me.

67
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:08,699
We find that as the apostle Paul sought the Lord

68
00:03:08,699 --> 00:03:11,320
and received an answer from God,

69
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:13,820
by the way, aren't you thankful that you can pray?

70
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:15,279
Aren't you thankful that you have a God

71
00:03:15,279 --> 00:03:16,740
who hears and answers,

72
00:03:16,740 --> 00:03:19,300
that is able to do exceeding abundantly

73
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:20,940
above all that we ask or think?

74
00:03:20,979 --> 00:03:23,139
And I believe this morning with all my heart,

75
00:03:23,139 --> 00:03:25,039
even as I mentioned last week,

76
00:03:25,039 --> 00:03:27,779
that God could have removed the thorn.

77
00:03:28,740 --> 00:03:33,059
It was within God's power to have that thorn removed,

78
00:03:33,059 --> 00:03:36,960
but God chose instead really to do something

79
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:39,559
that I believe is even greater,

80
00:03:39,559 --> 00:03:42,660
and that is this, to give his grace

81
00:03:42,660 --> 00:03:47,660
and to ensure his servant that it, his grace, was sufficient.

82
00:03:48,199 --> 00:03:53,080
And these verses of scripture are so profoundly impactful

83
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:54,880
in the lives of God's people,

84
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:57,419
and we live today in a society

85
00:03:57,419 --> 00:04:00,559
that really prioritizes comfort,

86
00:04:00,559 --> 00:04:03,000
that prioritizes pleasure.

87
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:06,259
We live in that kind of a society.

88
00:04:06,259 --> 00:04:09,080
We find that as the last days are described

89
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:11,039
in 2 Timothy chapter three,

90
00:04:11,039 --> 00:04:14,520
and we've looked at, as we look at 2 Corinthians 12,

91
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,639
we've seen some of these things.

92
00:04:15,639 --> 00:04:16,859
We talked about boasters,

93
00:04:16,859 --> 00:04:19,480
and the scriptures talk about boasters

94
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:21,600
in 2 Timothy chapter three.

95
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:23,799
It talks about those that are lovers of pleasure

96
00:04:23,799 --> 00:04:25,320
more than lovers of God,

97
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:28,480
and we find that we live in a culture and a society

98
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:32,920
that prioritizes comfort, that prioritizes pleasure,

99
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:35,059
but we find that as we look at the perspective

100
00:04:35,059 --> 00:04:38,000
of the apostle Paul in these verses of scripture,

101
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,320
that it stands in stark contrast

102
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:42,279
to the philosophy of the day.

103
00:04:43,279 --> 00:04:46,239
I believe that this portion of scripture,

104
00:04:46,239 --> 00:04:49,160
like many others, are a challenge to us.

105
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:52,720
God gives us his word to comfort us,

106
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,839
to convict us, to challenge us,

107
00:04:54,839 --> 00:04:58,119
and all at the same time, God's word is able to do that.

108
00:04:58,119 --> 00:05:00,399
I'm thankful that God's word is powerful

109
00:05:00,399 --> 00:05:04,079
and that it's profitable and that God uses his word,

110
00:05:04,079 --> 00:05:06,200
and God uses his servants.

111
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:10,040
There are times in which we're looking at the apostle Paul,

112
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:11,399
and as you study the New Testament,

113
00:05:11,399 --> 00:05:12,279
and you study his life,

114
00:05:12,279 --> 00:05:14,720
there are times in which we think of Paul

115
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:18,640
in a manner in which Paul would not want us to think of him.

116
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:20,559
We don't, sometimes we don't say it,

117
00:05:20,559 --> 00:05:22,440
but maybe we have that perspective

118
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:25,160
that he's some kind of a super Christian

119
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,640
and so on and so forth,

120
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:29,799
and Paul would not want people to think that way of him.

121
00:05:29,799 --> 00:05:33,160
In fact, he says that he's the chiefest of sinners.

122
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,899
He says even in the text of scripture

123
00:05:34,899 --> 00:05:37,239
in 2 Corinthians chapter 12 at verse number six,

124
00:05:37,239 --> 00:05:39,720
lest any man should think of me above that

125
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:42,359
which he seeth me to be or that he heareth of me.

126
00:05:42,359 --> 00:05:45,480
Paul understood the importance of humility,

127
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:46,920
but when we look at the apostle Paul,

128
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:50,119
and many times we look at some of the perspectives of Paul

129
00:05:50,119 --> 00:05:55,119
as he shares his heart under the different writings

130
00:05:55,119 --> 00:05:56,760
to churches and to individuals,

131
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,880
and he's giving to us truth,

132
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:02,279
and we really see that this is how God was working

133
00:06:02,279 --> 00:06:04,200
in the life of an individual,

134
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:05,799
and here's what I'm thankful for this morning.

135
00:06:05,799 --> 00:06:06,959
Right at the beginning of the message,

136
00:06:06,959 --> 00:06:08,239
here's what I'm thankful for.

137
00:06:08,239 --> 00:06:11,279
God is no respecter of persons.

138
00:06:11,279 --> 00:06:13,880
God will work in your life

139
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:16,500
in the same way he worked in Paul's life.

140
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:19,959
God will use you in the same way that he used Paul.

141
00:06:19,959 --> 00:06:20,799
You know what's different?

142
00:06:20,799 --> 00:06:23,019
Paul made himself available to God.

143
00:06:23,019 --> 00:06:24,880
Paul has that mindset.

144
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:27,239
We often quote at Galatians 2.20,

145
00:06:27,239 --> 00:06:28,559
I won't quote the whole verse,

146
00:06:28,559 --> 00:06:32,059
but he says I am crucified with Christ.

147
00:06:32,059 --> 00:06:34,579
Living that crucified life,

148
00:06:34,579 --> 00:06:38,079
understanding that for me to live as Christ

149
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,200
and to die is gain,

150
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:43,440
and Paul had this eternal perspective

151
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:48,359
that so impacted every aspect of his life.

152
00:06:48,359 --> 00:06:50,799
What happens sometimes if we're not careful

153
00:06:50,799 --> 00:06:54,239
is that we can get our focus off of the eternal things

154
00:06:54,239 --> 00:06:55,880
and onto the temporal things

155
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:57,859
because we do live in this world,

156
00:06:57,859 --> 00:07:00,040
though we are not of this world,

157
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:01,920
and we find that there are times

158
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:04,519
in which we can become distracted,

159
00:07:04,519 --> 00:07:06,880
and here as we look at the passage of Scripture

160
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,239
in verse nine and 10,

161
00:07:08,239 --> 00:07:10,000
I really wanna focus this morning

162
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:13,380
on how Paul responded to the answer

163
00:07:13,380 --> 00:07:15,239
that he received from God.

164
00:07:16,239 --> 00:07:19,480
Sometimes we get an answer like Paul did

165
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:22,179
that may not be the answer we were looking for.

166
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:25,519
How do we respond?

167
00:07:25,519 --> 00:07:27,100
Well, let me ask you this.

168
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:29,799
Have you ever seen a toddler respond to no?

169
00:07:29,799 --> 00:07:33,679
Have you ever witnessed that?

170
00:07:33,679 --> 00:07:36,220
Do they like it?

171
00:07:36,579 --> 00:07:41,380
Generally speaking, does a toddler like no?

172
00:07:42,739 --> 00:07:44,140
No.

173
00:07:44,140 --> 00:07:46,459
Does a teenager like no?

174
00:07:46,459 --> 00:07:48,700
I mean, we can just keep going this morning, amen?

175
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:51,019
I mean, does an adult, does a senior citizen?

176
00:07:51,019 --> 00:07:52,799
We don't like no.

177
00:07:52,799 --> 00:07:54,619
We want what we want.

178
00:07:54,619 --> 00:07:57,420
Am I telling the truth this morning?

179
00:07:57,420 --> 00:08:00,940
Our little granddaughter, two and a few months old,

180
00:08:00,940 --> 00:08:02,220
I know like no.

181
00:08:03,779 --> 00:08:05,899
She already has figured it out, all right?

182
00:08:06,619 --> 00:08:09,179
When Juliana says no, Nova is like,

183
00:08:09,179 --> 00:08:11,820
no, that's not the answer I was looking for.

184
00:08:11,820 --> 00:08:13,440
She wants the yes.

185
00:08:14,420 --> 00:08:18,119
How do we respond when God says no?

186
00:08:19,380 --> 00:08:21,700
When God gives an answer that's different

187
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:23,220
than what we were looking for?

188
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:27,140
I know that none of us would lay down on the floor

189
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:30,140
and throw a temper tantrum like a toddler would,

190
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:34,099
but God sees your heart.

191
00:08:35,059 --> 00:08:39,059
And maybe internally, you're throwing a temper tantrum

192
00:08:39,059 --> 00:08:42,059
when God doesn't answer the way that you want Him to answer.

193
00:08:43,859 --> 00:08:45,780
And the reality this morning is that when we look

194
00:08:45,780 --> 00:08:48,020
at this passage of Scripture,

195
00:08:48,020 --> 00:08:51,140
God provides us with a perspective

196
00:08:51,140 --> 00:08:55,200
that is worthy of our review.

197
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:59,380
And I trust that it would impact us this morning.

198
00:08:59,380 --> 00:09:02,000
There are times in which we read of the life of Paul

199
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,500
when he says in Philippians,

200
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:06,200
I have learned in whatsoever state I am there with

201
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,039
to be content.

202
00:09:07,039 --> 00:09:10,359
And I've often said to you that I can't say like Paul said,

203
00:09:10,359 --> 00:09:13,479
I have learned, but what I try to say is I am learning.

204
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:17,099
I look at this passage of Scripture and I say,

205
00:09:17,099 --> 00:09:21,479
God, I want to be able to say this.

206
00:09:21,479 --> 00:09:23,039
But the reality is I don't know

207
00:09:23,039 --> 00:09:26,219
that I'm there every day of my life.

208
00:09:26,219 --> 00:09:28,039
Notice what he says in verse number nine,

209
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:31,280
and he, God says to Paul, and he said unto me,

210
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:33,640
this is the answer to the request,

211
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:35,599
God, would you let it depart from me?

212
00:09:35,599 --> 00:09:39,280
My grace is sufficient for thee.

213
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,159
Notice what he says,

214
00:09:40,159 --> 00:09:44,039
for my strength is made perfect in weakness.

215
00:09:44,039 --> 00:09:47,080
Most gladly, this is what Paul's response is

216
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:49,159
to the answer that God gives.

217
00:09:49,159 --> 00:09:53,640
Most gladly, therefore, will I rather glory

218
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:55,479
in my infirmities,

219
00:09:55,479 --> 00:09:59,760
that the power of Christ may rest upon me.

220
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:00,599
Verse.

221
00:10:00,599 --> 00:10:09,879
Verse 10, Therefore I take pleasure in infirmities, in reproaches, in necessities, in persecutions,

222
00:10:09,879 --> 00:10:13,559
in distresses, for Christ's sake.

223
00:10:13,559 --> 00:10:17,739
For when I am weak, then am I strong.

224
00:10:17,739 --> 00:10:22,119
This is Paul's response to the answer that God gave.

225
00:10:22,119 --> 00:10:29,079
This is Paul truly embracing the promise that God gave in the answer because God's promise

226
00:10:29,079 --> 00:10:35,679
in the answer is my grace is sufficient for thee.

227
00:10:35,679 --> 00:10:37,359
He didn't say that it might be.

228
00:10:37,359 --> 00:10:39,359
He didn't say that I hope it will be.

229
00:10:39,359 --> 00:10:43,199
He said my grace is sufficient for thee.

230
00:10:43,199 --> 00:10:50,919
And then he said this for my strength, God's strength is made perfect in weakness.

231
00:10:50,919 --> 00:10:53,599
Paul says this at the end of verse number 10.

232
00:10:53,599 --> 00:10:58,319
He says that the power of Christ may rest upon me.

233
00:10:58,319 --> 00:11:03,199
Let me ask you this morning, do you want God's power?

234
00:11:03,199 --> 00:11:05,199
Do you want God's power?

235
00:11:05,199 --> 00:11:11,679
I mean, do you truly desire that whatever is necessary that you will give yourself as

236
00:11:11,679 --> 00:11:18,599
that vessel that I would say, as the songwriter said, I surrender all because truly I want

237
00:11:18,599 --> 00:11:22,199
God's power to rest upon me.

238
00:11:22,199 --> 00:11:27,879
I recognize that without him I can do nothing, that without him I am nothing, and I need

239
00:11:27,959 --> 00:11:35,719
God and I desire that God's power would rest upon me.

240
00:11:35,719 --> 00:11:38,359
That's what Paul says.

241
00:11:38,359 --> 00:11:46,519
I've asked the question by way of title this morning, in what do you take pleasure?

242
00:11:46,519 --> 00:11:47,719
In what do you take pleasure?

243
00:11:47,719 --> 00:11:50,279
In what do you take pleasure?

244
00:11:50,279 --> 00:11:52,199
Let's look at it this morning.

245
00:11:52,199 --> 00:11:55,759
Notice if you're taking notes, number one, notice what Paul declared.

246
00:11:55,759 --> 00:11:57,319
Paul makes this declaration.

247
00:11:57,319 --> 00:12:02,399
He truly believed what the Lord told him, and he says most gladly therefore.

248
00:12:02,399 --> 00:12:06,999
He says in verse 10, therefore I take pleasure, and you see that the therefore is in verse

249
00:12:06,999 --> 00:12:12,159
number nine as well as verse number 10, and as Paul would use that word therefore, he's

250
00:12:12,159 --> 00:12:15,259
referring back to the answer that God gave.

251
00:12:15,259 --> 00:12:16,599
He was seeking God.

252
00:12:16,599 --> 00:12:21,439
He was seeking that God would give him the deliverance that he was asking for, and God's

253
00:12:21,439 --> 00:12:27,039
answer comes, my grace is sufficient for thee, for my strength is made perfect in weakness,

254
00:12:27,039 --> 00:12:34,479
and Paul says most gladly therefore, based upon what God has said, most gladly.

255
00:12:34,479 --> 00:12:35,519
Isn't that interesting?

256
00:12:35,519 --> 00:12:37,619
He didn't just say therefore I will.

257
00:12:37,619 --> 00:12:39,739
He didn't just say gladly I will.

